Package regexp

Class Summary
Fragment The Fragment class specifies the Fragment object, that is used in the generation of an NFA.
Main The Main class contains the main method of the regexp application.
NFA The NFA class contains a static method for converting a postfix-form (also known as reverse polish notation, RPN) regular expression into a Non-deterministic Finite Automata (NFA) that is used for evaluating if a certain character string matches the given regular expression.
NFAsimulation The NFAsimulation class contains the static method used for simulating an NFA.
OwnArrayList<E> The OwnArrayList specifies an explicit implementation of ArrayList, as demanded by Matti Luukkainen for the Data Structures Project course.
OwnStack<E> The OwnStack specifies an explicit implementation of Stack, as demanded by Matti Luukkainen for the Data Structures Project course.
Postfix The Postfix class contains the static methods used for converting a regular expression from infix to postfix (also known as Reverse Polish Notation) form.
State The State class specifies the State object, which is the basic building block of an NFA (Non-deterministic finite automata).
